com.github.robtimus.junit.support.test.collections

Interface MapTests.RemoveExactValueTests<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - The key type of the map to test.
    V - The value type of the map to test.
    All Superinterfaces:
    MapTests<K,V>
    Enclosing interface:
    MapTests<K,V>

    @TestInstance(value=PER_CLASS)
 @DisplayName(value="remove(Object, Object)")
public static interface MapTests.RemoveExactValueTests<K,V>
extends MapTests<K,V>
    Contains tests for Map.remove(Object, Object).

    By default, the tests in this interface assume that calling Map.remove(Object, Object) with a key or value that is null or an instance of an incompatible type will simply return false. If any of these is not the case, annotate your class with RemoveNullKeyNotSupported, RemoveNullNotSupported, RemoveIncompatibleKeyNotSupported and/or RemoveIncompatibleNotSupported.

    Author:
    Rob Spoor
